---
/**
 * EN — Pillar (W293): Solar panel prices in Morocco. Faithful translation of
 * /prix-panneaux-solaires-maroc — evergreen, every figure mirrors the FR 1:1
 * (same source: the dated blog post prix-installation-solaire-maroc-2026).
 * Internal links use localizeNavHref (EN/AR if available, else the existing
 * FR page — never a dead link). FR untouched.
 */
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import V2Enhance from '../../components/V2Enhance.astro';
import Article33Ribbon from '../../components/Article33Ribbon.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import CtaBand from '../../components/CtaBand.astro';
import StickyCta from '../../components/StickyCta.astro';
import RelatedLinks from '../../components/RelatedLinks.astro';
import { NAP } from '../../lib/nap';
import { getLocaleFromPath } from '../../i18n/utils';
import { localizeNavHref } from '../../i18n/pages';

const locale = getLocaleFromPath(Astro.url.pathname);
const L = (href: string) => localizeNavHref(href, locale);

const verifiedDate = new Date('2026-07-03');
const dateFmt = new Intl.DateTimeFormat('en-GB', { day: 'numeric', month: 'long', year: 'numeric' });

const fourchettes = [
  { kwc: '3 kWc', prix: '28,000 – 42,000 DH' },
  { kwc: '5 kWc', prix: '45,000 – 65,000 DH' },
  { kwc: '10 kWc', prix: '85,000 – 120,000 DH' },
];

const url = new URL(Astro.url.pathname, Astro.site).href;
const schemaImageUrl = new URL('/og/residentiel.png', Astro.site).href;
const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: 'Solar panel prices in Morocco: indicative brackets by power',
  description: 'How much does a turnkey solar installation cost in Morocco, by power (kWc), with roof, battery and VAT surcharges — indicative brackets, reviewed every year.',
  image: schemaImageUrl,
  about: { '@type': 'Thing', name: 'Solar installation price Morocco' },
  author: { '@type': 'Organization', name: NAP.name, url: NAP.url },
  publisher: { '@type': 'Organization', name: NAP.name, url: NAP.url },
  mainEntityOfPage: url,
};
---

<Layout
  title="Solar panel prices in Morocco: brackets by power (kWc) | Taqinor"
  description="How much does a turnkey solar installation cost in Morocco? Indicative brackets by power (3, 5, 10 kWc), roof and battery surcharges, VAT, and why the real figure always comes from a technical visit."
  ogSlug="residentiel"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(jsonLd)} />
  <div class="v2">
    <V2Enhance />
    <Article33Ribbon />

    <Breadcrumb items={[{ label: 'Home', href: L('/') }, { label: 'Solar panel prices in Morocco' }]} />

    <article class="mx-auto max-w-[68ch] px-4 pb-24 pt-12 sm:pb-28">
      <p class="tech-label v2-kicker rule-brass text-lune">Prices & brackets</p>
      <h1 class="display v2-page-title mt-5 text-white">Solar panel prices in Morocco</h1>

      <p class="guide-byline mt-3 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-2 gap-y-1 text-xs text-lune-faint">
        <span>Brackets reviewed {dateFmt.format(verifiedDate)} · by Reda Kasri</span>
      </p>

      <p class="v2-lead mt-6 text-lune-soft">
        "How much does it really cost?" is the first question in almost every one of our meetings.
        This page gathers Moroccan-market order-of-magnitude figures, with their sources and their
        limits — not a firm price, but enough to budget with and to spot an offer that's abnormally
        low or abnormally expensive before your quote.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display v2-section-title mt-12 text-white">Turnkey brackets by power</h2>
      <p class="v2-lead mt-5 text-lune-soft">
        These prices cover both the equipment supply <strong class="text-white">and</strong> the
        full installation (inverter, wiring, structure, commissioning). They are drawn from Moroccan
        installer publications and online price guides — <strong class="text-white">indicative
        brackets</strong>, not official rates.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="v2-lead w-full border-collapse text-left text-sm text-lune-soft">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/20 text-white">
              <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-bold">Installed power</th>
              <th class="py-3 font-bold">Indicative bracket (MAD incl. VAT)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {fourchettes.map((f) => (
              <tr class="border-b border-white/10">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-bold text-white">{f.kwc}</td>
                <td class="py-3">{f.prix}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="v2-lead mt-5 text-lune-soft">
        <strong class="text-white">Average turnkey cost: about 10,000 – 14,000 DH/kWc</strong>
        (equipment + labour — sources: solaropeak.com, ecovolt.ma, electrosolarplus.ma,
        lechantier.ma). The spread reflects roof type, distance to the electrical panels, inverter
        brand and installer margins. An on-site quote remains essential.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display v2-section-title mt-12 text-white">Beware of "4,700 DH/kWc" prices</h2>
      <p class="v2-lead mt-5 text-lune-soft">
        You'll often see a price around <strong class="text-white">4,700 DH/kWc</strong> or even
        lower circulating. That figure corresponds to the <strong class="text-white">equipment kit
        cost alone</strong> (panels + inverter, excluding installation, wiring, structure,
        connection) — implausibly low for a finished turnkey installation. Don't compare that figure
        to the brackets above: they are two different realities.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display v2-section-title mt-12 text-white">Surcharges depending on roof configuration</h2>
      <p class="v2-lead mt-5 text-lune-soft">
        Not all roofs are alike. Some configurations add significant costs to the base bracket:
      </p>
      <ul class="v2-lead mt-5 list-disc space-y-3 pl-6 text-lune-soft">
        <li><strong class="text-white">Tile or corrugated-sheet roofs</strong> (more technical installation): +6,000 – 12,000 DH</li>
        <li><strong class="text-white">Steep slope (&gt; 30°)</strong>: +4,000 – 8,000 DH for safety equipment and installation complexity</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="v2-lead mt-5 text-lune-soft">
        A concrete terrace with easy access remains the least costly configuration. If your roof is
        steep or made of fragile materials, budget for this surcharge — see also our guide
        <a href={L('/guides/mon-toit-peut-il-supporter-des-panneaux')} class="border-b border-azur-200/60 pb-0.5 font-semibold text-azur-200 transition-colors hover:text-white">can my roof support panels?</a>
      </p>

      <h2 class="display v2-section-title mt-12 text-white">The battery question: useful, but not cost-neutral</h2>
      <p class="v2-lead mt-5 text-lune-soft">
        A <strong class="text-white">battery-less</strong> installation (grid-connected) remains the
        most common and most profitable solution for most urban homes. If you want to store energy
        for the evening or protect against outages, an LFP battery adds a significant cost:
      </p>
      <ul class="v2-lead mt-5 list-disc space-y-3 pl-6 text-lune-soft">
        <li><strong class="text-white">LFP battery 5 – 15 kWh: +22,000 – 60,000 MAD</strong> depending on capacity and brand</li>
        <li>The payback period stretches by <strong class="text-white">1 to 3 years</strong> with a battery</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="v2-lead mt-5 text-lune-soft">
        Our guide <a href={L('/guides/quelle-taille-de-batterie')} class="border-b border-azur-200/60 pb-0.5 font-semibold text-azur-200 transition-colors hover:text-white">what battery size?</a> details the sizing tiers and why, in Morocco, storing pays off more than exporting.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display v2-section-title mt-12 text-white">VAT and customs duties</h2>
      <p class="v2-lead mt-5 text-lune-soft">
        The tax regime is not uniform: bare panels are exempt from VAT (with no input-VAT
        deduction), a turnkey installation (supply + install) is subject to
        <strong class="text-white"> 20 % VAT</strong> — the brackets on this page are stated
        including VAT for individuals. Customs duties on imported inverters dropped from 17.5 % to
        2.5 %, which has helped push their market cost down.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display v2-section-title mt-12 text-white">Return on investment: 5 to 7 years residential</h2>
      <p class="v2-lead mt-5 text-lune-soft">
        The payback period most often cited by Moroccan installers for a standard residential
        installation (without battery) is <strong class="text-white">5 to 7 years</strong>. With a
        battery, add 1 to 3 more years. This calculation depends heavily on your actual consumption
        and your ONEE tariff bracket — see our
        <a href={L('/financement')} class="border-b border-azur-200/60 pb-0.5 font-semibold text-azur-200 transition-colors hover:text-white">financing & returns</a>
        page for detail, and the article
        <a href={L('/blog/rentabilite-solaire-par-ville-maroc')} class="border-b border-azur-200/60 pb-0.5 font-semibold text-azur-200 transition-colors hover:text-white">profitability by city</a>
        for regional figures.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display v2-section-title mt-12 text-white">How many panels do you need?</h2>
      <p class="v2-lead mt-5 text-lune-soft">
        Before comparing prices, you need to know the right power for your household. A household
        consuming between 4,000 and 6,000 kWh/year generally needs 3 to 5 kWc; between 6,000 and
        10,000 kWh/year, more like 5 to 8 kWc. Our dedicated guide covers the full method:
        <a href={L('/guides/combien-de-panneaux-pour-ma-maison')} class="border-b border-azur-200/60 pb-0.5 font-semibold text-azur-200 transition-colors hover:text-white">how many panels for my house?</a>
      </p>

      <h2 class="display v2-section-title mt-12 text-white">A last word before signing anything</h2>
      <p class="v2-lead mt-5 text-lune-soft">
        Use these brackets to budget and to spot an offer that's abnormally low or abnormally
        expensive. But don't ask them for what they can't give: a firm price. Your roof
        configuration, your consumption, your ONEE bracket and the distance between the panels and
        the electrical panel move the final total, sometimes by several thousand dirhams. The only
        figure that counts for your house comes from reading your bill and a visit — free and with
        no obligation.
      </p>
      <p class="v2-lead mt-3 text-xs text-lune-faint">
        For the full 2026 pricing update (equipment/labour split, worked examples), see our article
        <a href={L('/blog/prix-installation-solaire-maroc-2026')} class="border-b border-white/40 pb-0.5 font-semibold text-white transition-colors hover:border-white">How much does a solar installation cost in Morocco in 2026?</a>
      </p>

      <RelatedLinks links={[
        { href: L('/résidentiel'), label: 'Our residential solutions' },
        { href: L('/nos-solutions'), label: 'All our solutions' },
        { href: L('/guides'), label: 'All the guides' },
        { href: L('/blog'), label: 'The blog' },
      ]} />
    </article>

    <CtaBand title="The only figure that matters is yours. Launch the free study." href={L('/devis/mon-toit')} />

    <StickyCta />
  </div>
</Layout>
